---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'how-pec-works', text: 'How Pre-Existing Conditions Work', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Impact', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Pre-Existing Conditions Guide', href: '/guides/pre-existing-conditions-abroad' },
  { title: 'Chronic Conditions Coverage', href: '/guides/chronic-conditions-coverage' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'PEC Approach', allianz: 'Moratorium or MHD', bupa: 'Full Medical Underwriting', cigna: 'Full Medical Underwriting' },
  { feature: 'Typical Waiting Period', allianz: '12-24 months', bupa: '12-24 months', cigna: '12-24 months' },
  { feature: 'Diabetes Coverage', allianz: 'Often covered', bupa: 'Case-by-case', cigna: 'Often excluded' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health History', allianz: 'More flexible', bupa: 'Strict exclusions', cigna: 'Very strict' },
  { feature: 'Heart Conditions', allianz: 'Underwritten', bupa: 'Underwritten', cigna: 'Often excluded' },
  { feature: 'Continuation Options', allianz: 'Good', bupa: 'Excellent', cigna: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Premium Loading', allianz: 'Moderate', bupa: 'Higher', cigna: 'Standard' },
  { feature: 'Best For', allianz: 'Most flexible', bupa: 'Premium service', cigna: 'Healthy applicants' },
];

const conditionColumns = [
  { key: 'condition', header: 'Condition' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const conditionRows = [
  { condition: 'Type 2 Diabetes (controlled)', allianz: 'Often covered', bupa: 'May be covered', cigna: 'Usually excluded' },
  { condition: 'Hypertension (managed)', allianz: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', cigna: 'Usually covered' },
  { condition: 'Asthma', allianz: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', cigna: 'Usually covered' },
  { condition: 'Depression/Anxiety history', allianz: 'May be covered', bupa: 'Often excluded', cigna: 'Usually excluded' },
  { condition: 'Heart disease history', allianz: 'Case-by-case', bupa: 'Case-by-case', cigna: 'Often excluded' },
  { condition: 'Cancer (in remission)', allianz: 'Waiting period', bupa: 'Waiting period', cigna: 'Often excluded' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz vs Bupa vs Cigna: Best Insurance for Pre-Existing Conditions 2026"
  description="Compare how Allianz Care, Bupa Global, and Cigna Global handle pre-existing conditions. Coverage options, waiting periods, and which insurer is most likely to cover your condition."
  headline="Allianz vs Bupa vs Cigna: Pre-Existing Condition Coverage Compared"
  subheadline="Not all insurers treat pre-existing conditions equally. Here's who's most likely to cover you—and what it will cost."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Most Flexible</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Moratorium option, more lenient underwriting. Best chance of getting coverage for many conditions.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best for Continuation</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best option if switching from another insurer. Lifetime renewal. Can negotiate coverage.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Strictest Underwriting</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Great insurer but stricter on pre-existing conditions. Best for healthy applicants.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    If you have pre-existing conditions, your insurer choice matters more than anything else. Allianz is the most flexible, often covering conditions that Cigna and Bupa exclude. Bupa sits in the middle but excels at continuation coverage. Cigna has the best service but strictest underwriting.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Most Flexible</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Moratorium Option</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Value</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care is the most accommodating of the three for pre-existing conditions. They offer both moratorium underwriting (conditions excluded initially, covered later if stable) and full medical underwriting. Their underwriters tend to be more lenient, especially for well-managed chronic conditions.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Pre-existing condition approach:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Moratorium option:</strong> Skip detailed medical questions; conditions excluded for 24 months, then covered if no treatment needed</li>
    <li><strong>MHD (Medical History Disregarded):</strong> Available for groups and some individual plans</li>
    <li><strong>Full underwriting:</strong> More lenient than competitors</li>
    <li>Mental health history treated more favorably</li>
    <li>Diabetes often covered with proper documentation</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> People with chronic conditions who've been declined elsewhere. Those with mental health history. Anyone wanting the moratorium option.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Continuation Expert</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Lifetime Renewal</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Service</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global takes a middle approach. They're strict on new applicants with conditions, but excel at continuation coverage—transferring from another insurer without losing coverage for existing conditions. Their lifetime renewal guarantee means once you're in, you stay in.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Pre-existing condition approach:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Full medical underwriting:</strong> Every condition reviewed individually</li>
    <li><strong>Continuation coverage:</strong> Best in class—can transfer from previous insurer</li>
    <li><strong>Premium loading:</strong> May charge more rather than exclude</li>
    <li><strong>Lifetime renewal:</strong> Can't be dropped for developing conditions</li>
    <li>More willing to negotiate coverage terms</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Those switching from another international insurer. People who want guarantees they won't be dropped. Those willing to pay more for coverage.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Strict Underwriting</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Healthy Applicants</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global has the best service, app, and claims processing—but they're the strictest on pre-existing conditions. If you're healthy, Cigna is excellent. If you have conditions, you may face permanent exclusions that Allianz or Bupa would cover.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Pre-existing condition approach:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Full medical underwriting:</strong> Strictest of the three</li>
    <li><strong>More likely to exclude:</strong> Especially for metabolic, cardiac, mental health</li>
    <li><strong>Clear yes/no answers:</strong> Less negotiation than Bupa</li>
    <li><strong>Consistent worldwide:</strong> Same underwriting globally</li>
    <li>Once covered, excellent claims experience</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Healthy applicants who want the best service. Those with minor, well-controlled conditions only. People who prioritize claims experience over underwriting flexibility.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Personalized Quotes"
    description="Describe your conditions and get quotes from all three insurers to see what coverage you can get."
    buttonText="Request Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="how-pec-works">How Pre-Existing Condition Coverage Works</h2>

  <h3>Common Coverage Outcomes</h3>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={conditionColumns} rows={conditionRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">
    *These are general patterns, not guarantees. Individual cases vary based on severity, control, time since diagnosis, and documentation.
  </p>

  <h3>Types of Underwriting</h3>

  <p><strong>Full Medical Underwriting (FMU):</strong> You disclose everything. Insurer reviews each condition and decides to cover, exclude, or add waiting period. Cigna and Bupa use this exclusively.</p>

  <p><strong>Moratorium Underwriting:</strong> No detailed medical questions upfront. Pre-existing conditions automatically excluded for 24 months. After 24 months symptom-free, condition is covered. Allianz offers this option.</p>

  <p><strong>Medical History Disregarded (MHD):</strong> All conditions covered from day one. Only available for groups or at high premiums. Allianz sometimes offers this.</p>

  <h3>Waiting Periods vs Permanent Exclusions</h3>

  <p>
    There's a big difference between a 12-24 month waiting period (condition will eventually be covered) and a permanent exclusion (never covered). Allianz tends toward waiting periods; Cigna tends toward permanent exclusions.
  </p>

  <h2 id="pricing">How Pre-Existing Conditions Affect Pricing</h2>

  <p>
    Having pre-existing conditions affects your premium in different ways:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Moderate premium loading (10-25% typical), more likely to cover with waiting period</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Higher premium loading (20-50% possible), but more likely to cover than exclude</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Standard pricing but stricter exclusions—pay same but get less coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The trade-off: Allianz and Bupa may charge more but actually cover your conditions. Cigna may quote lower but exclude important coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have been declined by other insurers</li>
        <li>Have mental health history</li>
        <li>Have Type 2 diabetes or metabolic conditions</li>
        <li>Want the moratorium option</li>
        <li>Prefer waiting periods to permanent exclusions</li>
        <li>Want comprehensive coverage at competitive prices</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are switching from another international insurer</li>
        <li>Want lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
        <li>Are willing to pay more for coverage</li>
        <li>Have conditions but want to negotiate terms</li>
        <li>Value premium service and support</li>
        <li>Plan to stay with one insurer long-term</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are healthy with minor conditions only</li>
        <li>Have well-controlled conditions unlikely to be excluded</li>
        <li>Prioritize service and claims experience</li>
        <li>Want the best digital experience</li>
        <li>Can accept exclusions for specific conditions</li>
        <li>Value app quality and fast processing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Should I disclose all my conditions?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, always. Non-disclosure can void your policy entirely when you make a claim. Insurers can access medical records. It's always better to be upfront and know what's covered than to face a denied claim later.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I'm declined by all three?</h3>
  <p>
    Try working with an international insurance broker who can access multiple markets. Some conditions are insurable through specialized underwriters. Local insurance in your destination country may also be an option—some countries have guaranteed-issue health insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Can pre-existing conditions become covered over time?</h3>
  <p>
    With Allianz's moratorium option: yes, after 24 months symptom-free. With full underwriting: some insurers review exclusions after 2-5 years of policy history. Ask your insurer about their review policy.
  </p>

  <h3>What counts as a pre-existing condition?</h3>
  <p>
    Any condition you had symptoms of, were diagnosed with, or received treatment for before your policy start date. This includes conditions you weren't formally diagnosed with but had symptoms of. Most insurers look back 5 years, some longer.
  </p>

  <h3>Does controlled mean covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Not automatically. "Well-controlled" conditions may still be excluded or have waiting periods. But good control, regular monitoring, and compliance with treatment make coverage more likely. Bring documentation of your condition management.
  </p>

  <h3>What about conditions that develop while insured?</h3>
  <p>
    Conditions that develop after your policy starts are covered like any other claim—they're not pre-existing. This is why getting insured while healthy is valuable. All three insurers cover conditions that develop during your coverage period.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Underwriting decisions are made case-by-case. What's covered for one person may be excluded for another. Get actual quotes with your medical information for accurate coverage terms.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
